        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "&c. — He speaks to his scholars with paternal authority and affection, to render them more attentive and obedient. Teachers among the Hebrews were commonly called ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "fathers, ",
        "children": []
