      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "sons. Hear the instruction of thy father — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "His good and wholesome counsels; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and forsake not the law of thy mother — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Those pious instructions which thy mother instilled into thee in thy tender years. This he adds, because children, when grown up, are very prone to slight their mothers’ advice, because of the infirmity of their sex, and because they have not that dependance upon, and expectation from their mothers, which they have from their fathers. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "They shall be an ornament, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "&c. — This will make thee amiable and honourable in the sight of God and of men, whereas the forsaking of those good counsels will make thee contemptible.",
