            "text": ", and what is said of the parents in one passage is in ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Proverbs 10:1",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " divided into two synonymous parallel passages. The stricter musar, which expresses the idea of sensible means of instruction (discipline), (",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Proverbs 13:24",
            "children": []
          },
          {
